claim.claim-text:
19. A method, comprising:
using a noble gas ion beam to form a first channel and a second channel in a surface of a material, a portion of the material positioned between the channels having parallel walls and a mean thickness of 100 nm or less between the parallel walls;
detaching the portion of the material;
exposing a first surface of the detached portion to a plurality of charged particles; and
detecting particles leaving a second surface of the detached portion opposite to the first surface, wherein:
the first channel has a first side wall and a second side wall and the second channel has a third side wall and a fourth side wall.
